		{
			"name": "sync-one-call",
			"description": "Entrypoint #3 — sync one call (pull/SYNC). Fetches a single call from the provider by id and runs it through the full sync pipeline (dialerServicesManager.syncOneCall). All inputs are query params; integration-flavor is derived downstream from company-id + integration-id. SyncStats are logged, not returned. For the actual sync to succeed the company/integration must be CONNECTED and reachable (company 9001 in dev/seed-dialers-local.sql).",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "sync-one-call — once",
					"request": {
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/telephonysystems/sync-one-call?company-id=9001&integration-id=9001&providerCallId=REPLACE_PROVIDER_CALL_ID&callDate=2024-01-01T00:00:00Z",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"telephonysystems",
								"sync-one-call"
							],
							"query": [
								{
									"key": "company-id",
									"value": "9001"
								},
								{
									"key": "integration-id",
									"value": "9001"
								},
								{
									"key": "providerCallId",
									"value": "REPLACE_PROVIDER_CALL_ID"
								},
								{
									"key": "callDate",
									"value": "2024-01-01T00:00:00Z",
									"description": "ISO-8601. Required only for Amazon Connect; optional otherwise."
								},
								{
									"key": "callUrl",
									"value": "",
									"description": "Optional recording URL override.",
									"disabled": true
								}
							]
						},
						"description": "Fetches one call from the provider and runs the full sync pipeline. Expect 200 with body 'Done; check logs to see the sync results;' — the SyncStats are in the service logs, not the response. Replace providerCallId with a real provider call id; company-id + integration-id must resolve to a CONNECTED integration."
